cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze cultural descriptions in different language editions of Wikipedia. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves social network analysis and data mining, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of cross-cultural stereotypes and conflict, which could be related to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
